    </Parent_Relationships>
    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Refers to the style of German pottery produced in an area including Höhr-Grenzhausen and Grenzau after 1590.  It is characterized by a gray body, decorated with regularly placed incised or stamped figures or coats of arms and partially colored with cobalt blue or manganese purple.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000000/VP</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000099620/Legacy AAT data</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Se refiere al estilo de cerámica alemana producido en una área que incluye Höhr-Grenzhausen y Grenzau después de 1590. Se caracteriza por un cuerpo gris, decorado con figuras regularmente incisas o estampadas o escudos de armas y parcialmente colorada con cobalto azul o manganeso púrpura.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Spanish</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000131/CDBP-SNPC</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000051034/TAA database (2000-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Verwijst naar de Duitse aardewerkstijl die werd vervaardigd in een tijdperk waartoe ook de Höhr-Grenzhausen en Grenzau behoren, na 1590. Deze stijl kenmerkt zich door grijze objecten, gedecoreerd met regelmatig geplaatste, ingekerfde of gestempelde vormen, of wapenschilden, gedeeltelijk gekleurd met kobaltblauw of mangaanpaars.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Dutch</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000205/AAT-Ned</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000113770/AAT-Ned (1994-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000052378/Winkler Prins Encyclopedie (1990)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>指在西元１５９０年之後，於赫爾-格倫茨豪森和格倫造等地區發展出的德國陶器風格。其特色為灰色主體、飾以佈局規律的雕刻或印花之圖案或盾徽，部份塗上鈷藍色或錳紫色。</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Chinese (traditional)</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000250/AS-Academia Sinica</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000079740/AS-Academia Sinica data (2014-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
    </Descriptive_Notes>
